 seem right. I’ve realized we need to avoid using reflection directly unless the public API explicitly calls for it. Oh, and we’ve been using a shim for this. I think there’s room for improvement here, but I need to be cautious!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating build tasks**\\n\\nI’m thinking about some aspects of the build process. I might need to check my assertions, but it seems like a dynamic report with active coverage could be useful after testing the JVM agent. I’m considering if I should add task ordering; the `callerClassShimJar` depending on `callerClassShimClasses` seems logical since it’s from the source set output. Also, I need to remove the stale Scala shim and maybe clean up directories using bash before editing the build.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_iGTLpgvbKNnvaM56ojb4Va7i|fc_01a34b971ae9a67b0169fb1fff6448819caa882a784e1d8e8b", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rm -f tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-actor_2.13/1.1.5/src/callerClassShim/scala/sun/reflect/Reflection.scala && mkdir -p tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-actor_2.13/1.1.5/src/callerClassShim/java/sun/reflect"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 555, "output": 1717, "cacheRead": 38912, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41184, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778065382409, "responseId": "resp_01a34b971ae9a67b0169fb1fe70528819c857df2771d1c58b7"}}
