[thinking] 
[thinking] **Exploring Test Class Interactions**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering whether the `VirtualThreadSupport` test class initializes `Reflect` before `ReflectTest`. Both run in the same fork with the patch applied, which is a good sign. I wonder if I could use an explicit assertion to ensure that `Method.invoke` functions properly, but reflection may not allow that. Perhaps checking the classloader could work, though I’m not sure. I think I need to refine my approach and be more concise moving forward to clear up any uncertainties.
